description:
&lt;p&gt;Healthcare Assistant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced Rehabilitation Assistant with a&lt;strong&gt; passion for rehabilitation,&lt;/strong&gt; looking to consolidate your clinical skills? Would you like to work in a friendly and supportive multi-disciplinary team? Then join us to provide excellent therapy care at one of our bedded rehabilitation units in the heart of London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are expanding our bed capacity over the winter period and we have an opening for a Band 3 Rehabilitation Assistant to join our North West Bedded Rehabilitation team located at the Pembridge Rehabilitation Unit on a fixed term basis to end March 2021. This role offers an excellent opportunity to work as part of a multi-disciplinary team delivering holistic, client centred and evidence based care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pembridge Rehab unit is in-patient rehabilitation facility providing rehab for residents in the boroughs of Kensington &amp; Chelsea, Hammersmith &amp; Fulham, Westminster and Brent, who wish to maximise their independence following illness or injury. Common presentations include weakness post covid, MSK, geriatrics, falls, Parkinson’s, amputees and orthopaedics. Check out the CLCH trust twitter and webpages for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have an active role in developing your practice whilst delivering holistic rehabilitation and assessments for local residents staying on our bedded units. You will also have the chance to build and maintain key relationships with our acute, community and adult social care partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Effective time management skills are essential, as are excellent communication skills and a commitment to the principles and practices of effective MDT working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining a friendly and forward-thinking multidisciplinary service, which is committed to high standards of practice. We will support you in developing your clinical skills, as well as offer you the opportunity to participate in clinical governance activities and other policy and service developments. We are committed to developing staff through regular supervision, appraisals and support in CPD opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
